---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Partners - SkanPay"
  description="SkanPay helps payment apps, mobile wallets, and loyalty platforms explore QR payment opportunities for physical commerce."
  activePath="/partners/"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Partners</p>
    <h1>Connect mobile payment relationships to in-store checkout</h1>
    <p>For payment apps, wallets, and loyalty platforms, QR payment can create a bridge between digital engagement and real-world merchant transactions.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="grid three">
      <article class="card route-card">
        <span>App</span>
        <h3>Payment apps</h3>
        <p>Explore how an app-based payment experience can participate in store checkout through QR payment flows.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card route-card">
        <span>Wallet</span>
        <h3>Mobile wallets</h3>
        <p>Support wallet experiences that customers can use while standing in front of a merchant checkout.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card route-card">
        <span>Loyalty</span>
        <h3>Loyalty platforms</h3>
        <p>Link payment moments with rewards, offers, and repeat-customer engagement where appropriate.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section split">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Partner focus</p>
      <h2>Make the integration conversation concrete</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">SkanPay can help frame the operational questions partners need to answer before going deeper into payment flow implementation.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="split-panel">
      <h3>Topics to align on</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Customer scan and authorization experience</li>
        <li>Merchant confirmation and support expectations</li>
        <li>Store onboarding and checkout training needs</li>
        <li>General reporting and transaction status requirements</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
